The national leadership of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has named Bayelsa State Governor Duoye Diri as Chairman of the party’s National Campaign Council. The governor will lead 127 other members of the campaign council ahead of the July 16 governorship election in the state. A statement yesterday in Abuja by PDP National Organising Secretary Umar Bature said members of the team include the party’s 12 serving governors. They are: Governors Seyi Makinde (Oyo), Aminu Tambuwal (Sokoto), Okezie Ikpeazu (Abia), Udom Emmanuel (Akwa Ibom), Darius Ishaku (Taraba), Samuel Ortom (Benue), Godwin Obaseki (Edo), Ahmadu Fintiri (Adamawa), Bala Mohammed (Bauchi), Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi (Enugu) and Nyesom Wike (Rivers).   Herders kill man for knocking down cow in Badagry     Bridging skill gaps in plumbing     5G: Nigeria begins race for 4.4b global subscriptions   Other members include Prince Olagunsoye Oyinlola, Dr. Bukola Saraki, Dr. Olusegun Mimiko, Emeka Ihedioha, Chief Shuaibu Oyedokun, Charles Akintoye, Senator Biodun Olujimi. Also on the list are: Elder Yemi Akinwonmi, Eyitayo Jegede, Solomon Arase, among others. The statement also listed PDP National Chairman, Dr. Iyorchia Ayu, and all members of the party’s National Working Committee (NWC) as members. According to the statement, the campaign council members will be sworn in at 10 a.m tomorrow at the PDP Abuja national secretariat in Abuja.